The correct fix is to pad the vector of scalars to the next power of two before the cost analysis begins. The most appropriate place for this is at the beginning of the `BoUpSLP::getTreeCost` function. This ensures that all subsequent cost analysis within this function and its callees operates on a vector size that the shuffle cost model can handle.

